ter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Walter Burghull was born about 1290, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Walter Burghill about 1328, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1290–":"umbes 1290–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1300":"1300","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","about 1320":"umbes 1320","Abt 1290":"umbes 1290","Abt 1328":"umbes 1328","1290":"1290","Warwick, Warwickshire, England":"Warwick, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Baddington, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warwick, Engl":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1290–":"noin 1290–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1320":"1320","1350":"1350","about 1320":"noin 1320","Abt 1290":"noin 1290","Abt 1328":"noin 1328","1290":"1290","Warwick, Warwickshire, England":"Warwick, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Baddington, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Warwick, Engl":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1290–":"environ 1290–Décédée","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1300":"1300",